caption: My sister and I have gone here multiple times as she missed the plate lunches she had while working in Hawaii. Better comfort food tha an a burger and fries will ever be. And Ask for extra katsu sauce. Whatever you get... EXTRA KATSU

I work close to this place and I have to say that it’s free-kin awesome. They have Hawaiian food and it’s the real deal. I’ve tried about 85% of their dishes and I love them all. The place is very affordable. If you’re ever close by I suggest to stop by here and try it. You will not be disappointed.

This place is a hidden gem; it's a little difficult to find a Hawaiian food restaurant that isn't just poke-bowls. This place has everything I was looking for: Loco Moco, Teriyaki Chicken, Bulgogi style beef, short ribs, chicken and pork katsu...everything accompanied by amazing rice and macaroni salad. They had great social distancing rules in place, and even though I thought it was a little expensive for 2 meals and 2 drinks (about $30 bucks) at first, when the food came out I realized it was really about 6 portions of food.
Great BBQ chicken

It’s quite difficult to find a spot that serves Hawaiian food. Found this spot via social media and food looked so good. I’ve come here already two times by the time of this review and gotta say this place deserves the recognition it receives.  Due to the times we’re living in, I’m not able to dine-in and enjoy the island-themed restaurant nor enjoy the excellent service I’ve received despite just ordering to-go. What I believe to be the owner has been really friendly and the way she has it set up for contactless payments and social distancing is beyond expectation.  The food, most importantly, is phenomenal. Price-wise it is very fair for what you’re getting and you get very generous portion sizes. I’ve had the Katsu curry and the mixed BBQ plate between my two visits and enjoyed it with one of the Hawaiian sodas. Very hot and delicious. Nothing is over seasoned or salty and the cold macaroni salad is a great contrast to the hot meat and white rice. The mixed BBQ plate consisted of short ribs, chicken teriyaki (if not wrong) and bbq beef. Definitely the short ribs and chicken teriyaki are a must-have.  Overall, Aloha Eats has a variety of Hawaiian staples that reminds you of home even if you’re not from there! LOL Definitely look into coming here any time soon! Just be wary of the parking situation which tends to be hard to find.

I remember when I first discovered this place, it had been years since I gone home.  When I first stepped in and looked at the menu, I was overjoyed to see a menu very similar to L&L Drive Inn back home.  I love that everything is as close to authentic as possible.  Nothing changed or made to be trendy with the times.  Just well prepared Hawaiian style plate lunches, just like you would see back home or at any garage party.  If you're missing home or if you want the real taste of Hawaii, come here.  I'd only request you guys bring Garlic Chicken or Lau Lau to the menu.  Kind of hard, but one can dream right?!?!  Well done guys and thank you for bringing the taste up here!

Love this authentic Hawaiian food!! Spam musubi & bbq rib plate is so delicious!! I always do take out & the food is consistent, delicious, & made to order!! My only negative thing is my last take out order experience was awful. I went in to place an order...& i’ve never felt so unwanted. The lady at the front seemed so frustrated because I was placing in order. She huffed & puffed with a rude “anything else” after every dish I said. She gave me the wrong time to come back to get my food 3 freaking times. I was so frustrated. She was no help at all!!! I’d rather hear that my food will take an hour rather than coming back to check every time she told me. Again...i’m in the service industry so I make sure it’s clear when reviewing so I don’t seem like i’m nit picking... I know this a little whole in the wall spot so I get it...but at least smile & make people feel welcomed when they come into a business. If you don’t like interacting with people....you chose the wrong job! My first experience was good. I hope this younger women isn’t working the next time I come, i’ll have to be that person that asks for management & Id really hate to even do that. I only ask for good food & good service, hope it’s not too much to ask for!
